Avera is the essential modern home with crisp, sleek design and natural elements that create simplicity like a breath of fresh air. With efficient layouts and wide-open spaces, these homes are light and airy in just the right amounts. We know your home isn't just a collection of rooms, it's where life unfolds. Let it all begin with Avera. Prices are anticipated to start in the mid $500’s. The Jackson at Arden View!
Arden View is a fresh, new community of 15 homes in the Richmond Beach area of Shoreline that's tucked next to a permanent green space and a stone's throw from Seattle. Near enough to the water that you could feel a breeze off the waves, and some of the homes have a prime view of the Sound. Arden View is defined by luxurious comforts with a sleek sensibility. Modern, effervescent, and a sophisticated classic, this community is sure to be timeless and built to last. Arden View's homes feature Sundquist’s forward-thinking, “Designed for Better Living”® home designs, which run a gamut of square footages and layouts, ranging from a versatile 2,800 to about 4,800 square feet. Description: This Seattle Four Square is charming! The main living area is open and spacious and includes a dining room and family room with a view of the Ballard Bridge, Discovery Park, and Olympic Mountains. The kitchen is spacious with plenty of cabinet space and a recently added pantry. There is also plenty of space for an informal dining table. There are three bedrooms on the top floor. One bedroom has a windowed nook with a view of a 100 year old cedar just outside the window. There are high ceilings throughout the house. There have been updates most notably a mother in law apartment in the basement that is bright and cheery and has full amenities including a washer and dryer. Important design elements have been kept including the original fir floors, molding and windows, which add warmth to the overall feel of the house. Additional updates include the installation of an energy efficient heat pump with split level heating /cooling system, a stairway to the attic with reinforced flooring for storage, radiant heated tiled bathroom floor, and a washer and dryer on the bedroom level. The yard is enclosed and has a fountain which creates a garden refuge in the hustle and bustle of city life. This home is in the heart of three amazing communities; Fremont, Ballard and Phinney Ridge. Each neighborhood has a unique personality and there are so many opportunities to get out and explore including; outdoor markets, seasonal celebrations, unique artisan products and fresh produce. Restaurants and cafes are within walking distance in every direction. The basement apartment is perfect for an Airbnb. It has earning potential of $2400.00 per month as an Airbnb destination. The owners have provided lodging for travelers from all over the world.
Custom mid-century modern split level. Vaulted ceilings. Open floorplan. Lots of storage. Huge, teak deck. Fantastic outlook.

The Jackson at Arden View!
Arden View is a fresh, new community of 15 homes in the Richmond Beach area of Shoreline that's tucked next to a permanent green space and a stone's throw from Seattle. Near enough to the water that you could feel a breeze off the waves, and some of the homes have a prime view of the Sound. Arden View is defined by luxurious comforts with a sleek sensibility. Modern, effervescent, and a sophisticated classic, this community is sure to be timeless and built to last. Arden View's homes feature Sundquist’s forward-thinking, “Designed for Better Living”® home designs, which run a gamut of square footages and layouts, ranging from a versatile 2,800 to about 4,800 square feet. The homes are sweeping great room styled plans, with large, bright windows and sliders to flood the open space with natural light. Curl up by the fire with a steaming mug and a good book, share good times with great people in outdoor living spaces, or serve up something tasty in our gourmet kitchens. We know your home isn't just where you sleep, it's where you dream. Let it all begin with Arden View. Prices are anticipated to start in the high $700’s. We pride ourselves on homes designed for your life, the way you want to live it. At Sundquist, we do more than just build houses: we build homes, Designed for Better Living®.

Plan Description: The Astoria is one of our most popular floor plans. . This beautiful home features 3,664 sqft of luxurious living with 5 bedrooms and 3.75 baths. Guests are greeted in the spacious 2-story Foyer with a dramatic curved staircase and French doors opening to the Den. Entertain guests in the formal dining room, complete with gorgeous coffered ceiling with crown moldings. The butlers pantry provides extra storage with its walk-in pantry as well as extra space to prep and comes with a beautiful 50-capacity under counter wine fridge. The butler's pantry provides direct access from the dining room to the kitchen. In the kitchen you will find a culinary lovers dream. From the beautiful over-sized slab island to the stainless steel appliances. The Island is ideal for informal meals or just a gathering with friends and family. Adjacent to the kitchen, the Nook is the perfect space for your casual dining, while the covered patio is fabulous for additional entertaining or just relaxing. The main floor guest suite is picture perfect for friends and family visiting-whether it be short term or long term. The adjacent guest bath, with its beautiful designer touches and walk-in tiled shower, helps create a private and easily accessible space for your guests. The focus of the upper level is the fabulous master suite, with its soaring vaulted ceiling, that leads out to a wall of beautiful windows. It doesn't end there though. Walk through the rrench doors and you are led to the master en suite, which includes luxurious finishes, walk-in shower with tile surround and mud set, and a stunning free-standing soaking tub. The rest of the upper level features 3 bedrooms, a spacious bonus room, and 2 bathrooms; one of which is a Jack-and-Jill style between 2 of the bedrooms. It also has a conveniently located laundry room with additional storage.

Plan Description: The 3,603 square foot, 5-bedroom and 2.75-bath Belmont floor plan offers a generous helping of space and home features. On the main level, through double doors you'll find the spacious den off the foyer, perfect for a secluded work space. . In the next room over you'll find the formal dining room with its signature dramatic coffered ceiling. A butler's pantry featuring an abundance of storage space is strategically situated between the dining and kitchen areas. It features upper and lower cabinets and offers an additional prepping space and plenty of storage. The spectacular open kitchen features a generously sized island with a distinctive slab tabletop that offers a substantial workspace for cooking and entertaining. The kitchen also boasts an abundance of cabinets and drawers to keep food, small appliances, cutlery, and other culinary tools close at-hand. The adjacent eating nook leads directly to the large covered patio that's picture-perfect for morning coffee or entertaining outside. The appealing great room blends seamlessly into the rest of this warm, welcoming open area with its beautiful fireplace. A secluded main level bedroom can act as the home's 5th bedroom or as a convenient guest room. Its adjacent bath offers privacy for guests while remaining near the heart of the house. The mud room, a practical place for removing dirty outerwear and footwear, is likewise here. The spacious upper level features 4 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms, a laundry room, and a bonus room/6th bedroom. The master bedroom is carefully laid out with a vaulted ceiling and numerous windows to give this cherished room a dynamic feeling while remaining comfortable and peaceful. Only steps away, the master bath features beautiful finishes, and spa inspired shower and soaking tub. The master walk-in closet offers abundant amounts of closet space between the 2 generous closets that connect the master bedroom to the master bath.

Plan Description: The Broadway's 3,627 square feet of prime space features 5 bedrooms, 2.75 baths, a den, and so much more. . Upon entering the main level from the elegant double doors, you'll be greeted in the well-lit foyer. Through another set of fine double doors, you'll find the spacious den that can easily function as a quite home office. Past the staircase, an elegant dining room is crowned by a coffered ceiling that gives the space further depth and texture. Whether you're holding an intimate get-together or a large celebration, the adjacent kitchen confidently serves your needs. It features a large central slab island with a convenient breakfast bar and eye-catching ceiling detail. The nearby eating nook is perfect for casual dining and offers direct access to the covered patio outside. The great room features a beautiful natural gas fireplace that offers lots of warmth and character even before a fire is lit. A convenient guest room with an adjacent bathroom is ideal for short or long term guests. Upstairs, the loft's spacious area can host a relaxing seating area for reading or relaxing. As you enter the master suite through the double doors the first thing you'll notice is the beautiful vaulted ceiling. Immediately accessible from the bedroom is the master bathroom which includes a large soaking tub and a spa inspired walk-in shower. The large walk-in closet offers an abundant amount of space. The upper level features 3 additional bedrooms, a large laundry room, a bathroom and a spacious bonus room. The bonus room is sure to inspire your creativity with all its possible uses from a family room, media room, or as second home office upstairs. The Broadway has a 2-car garage on its main level.

Plan Description: Luxurious living defines the Fairwood's generous 2-story, 3,729 square foot floor plan with an open, flexible design with 5 bedrooms, 3.75 bathrooms, a bonus room, and a spacious 3 car garage. . From top-to-bottom, the Fairwood will undoubtedly be a home that fits your lifestyle. Entertaining is a breeze in the Fairwood home plan, thanks to the spacious kitchen with sturdy and easy-to-maintain slab counters. There are many places where a hungry audience can sample your cooking results whether it's in the formal dining room, featuring a coffered ceiling, or at the eating nook near the kitchen for a more casual dining atmosphere. You might even choose to stay in the kitchen where the generously sized slab island work space is ready to accommodate counter stools for gathering around the heart of the action. The enormous family room is sure to be a much-loved space with its breathtaking natural gas fireplace and views of the backyard and large patio. Connected to the family room is the eating nook that offers direct access outside to the picturesque and spacious patio that's primed for entertaining outdoors. On the main level, the 5th room of the home can easily alternate as a guest suite or as a den with its own convenient bath and large closet. Four of the home's bedrooms are situated upstairs, this upper level additionally features a Jack-and-Jill bathroom, a hallway bathroom, and a spa inspired master bathroom. The spacious bonus room can act as a family room, a playroom, or as an additional bedroom as it has a convenient closet. The secluded master suite is a revitalizing sanctuary with its soaring vaulted ceiling and wall of windows that keep the spacious room well-lit. The master bath is outfitted with a splendid soaking tub. The additional bathrooms have the same upscale aesthetics.

Plan Description: When you think about all the elements that go into your dream home: roomy, accessible space, and flexible yet versatile design, the Madison floor plan confidently meets your every need. . This 3,368 square foot, 5 bedroom, 2.75 bathroom home is sure to be your dream home. Enter through the distinctive front double doors, where you'll find yourself encountering one breathtaking feature after another like the soaring staircase with a dramatic curve. On the opposite side, another set of double doors lead into the home's spacious den that is set in a secluded corner to provide privacy. The series of rooms compromised of the formal dining area, kitchen, eating nook, and great room have a rare, one-of-kind flow you'll especially treasure if you enjoy cooking and entertaining. The dining room has a large picture-perfect window and an elegant coffered ceiling that's sure to impress. A pantry hallway bridges this room to the kitchen but also offers a slab work surface to prep meals on before serving. The gourmet kitchen is the heart and soul of the main level. The versatile generously sized slab island doubles as both a work surface for preparing meals and a comfy place to enjoy them. Of course, you can also have a casual eating experience in the eating nook next to it. As the meeting point of the kitchen and great room, the eating nook serves as a practical space for to eat meals and catch up on the day. Or take the entertaining outside to the large covered patio directly off the eating nook. A guest room, mud room, and accessible bathroom additionally be found on the main floor. Upstairs, the Madison offers 4 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms, a bonus room, and a conveniently located laundry room. The master suite maintains a sunny, relaxing ambiance with its high, vaulted ceilings and picturesque windows. The accompanying master bath is fitted with a soaking bath tub and a spa inspired shower area.
